      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The \"real-time\" workaround is the only professional call because a 6-hour outage violates the SLA and exposes the bank to immediate reputational damage, whereas the vulnerability is a known, patched issue that can be handled via a zero-downtime deployment. A scheduled outage is a last resort for unknown critical failures, not for applying standard patches, so choosing the maintenance page route is the safer, more responsible decision that protects both the business and your career.",
